Algorithm 2:
Start
Create a dictionary products with product names and their prices
Use dictionary comprehension to create a new dictionary dis_products
In the new dictionary,reduce each price by 10% using the formula: new_price = price -(price * 10/100)
Store the updated prices dis_products
Display the original dictionary
Display the dictionary with discounted prices 
Stop


Code 2:
products = {
        "Apple":100,
        "Milk":60,
        "Bread":40
        "Eggs":80
}
dis_products = {key:value * 0.9 for key,value in products.item()}
print("Original Prices:",products)
print("Prices after 10% discount:",dis_products)

